  "title": "غزل شمارهٔ ۲۱",
  "title_en": "عبید زاکانی — غزل شمارهٔ ۲۱",
  "level": "Advanced",
  "layout": "poem",
  "source": "ganjoor",
  "ganjoor_id": 23571,
  "ganjoor_url": "https://ganjoor.net/obeyd/divan-obeyd/ghazal-obeyd/sh21",
  "description": "A compact Obeid Zakani ghazal of longing and impossibility: the speaker cannot leave the beloved's quarter, cannot endure separation, and insists that love, wine, and remembrance are inseparable from life.",
  "translation": "To go out again from this land is not possible;\nto be a stranger again to the beloved's lane is not possible.\n\nBecause of those sweet lips, that lock of hair, and your face,\npatience, endurance, forbearance, and composure are not possible for me.\n\nO heart, strive, perhaps you may seize the hem of the beloved,\nfor union without seeking and waiting is not possible.\n\nFor me not to love cannot enter my head;\nfor me not to drink wine in spring is not possible.\n\nIn that land where we now are,\npassage is not possible even for the travelers of the morning breeze.\n\nObeid too, if from time to time he can manage a ghazal,\nlet him say that no keepsake sweeter than this is possible.",
  "full_text": "دگر برون شدنم زین دیار ممکن نیست\nدگر غریبیم از کوی یار ممکن نیست\n\nمرا از آن لب شیرین و زلف و عارض تو\nشکیب و طاقت و صبر و قرار ممکن نیست\n\nدلا بکوش مگر دامنش به دست آری\nکه وصل بی‌طلب و انتظار ممکن نیست\n\nمن اینکه عشق نورزم مرا به سر نرود\nمن اینکه می نخورم در بهار ممکن نیست\n\nدر آن دیار که ماییم حالیا آنجا\nمسافران صبا را گذار ممکن نیست\n\nعبید هم غزلی گاه گاه اگر بتوان\nبگو که خوشتر از این یادگار ممکن نیست",
